1
00:00:10,833 --> 00:00:12,600
<i> What are you doing here?</i>

2
00:00:12,733 --> 00:00:15,900
<i> Flor needs a job.</i>

3
00:00:16,033 --> 00:00:18,233
<i> Please take effect.</i>

4
00:00:18,367 --> 00:00:18,867
<i> Please.</i>

5
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:22,000
<i> No!</i>

6
00:00:22,133 --> 00:00:22,933
<i> No!</i>

7
00:00:23,067 --> 00:00:25,333
<i> Emma! No! You're not real!</i>

8
00:00:25,467 --> 00:00:26,567
<i> What's going on here?</i>

9
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:29,933
<i>- Jade!
- Take me away from her!</i>

10
00:00:30,067 --> 00:00:31,333
<i> Z-X took effect instantly.</i>

11
00:00:31,467 --> 00:00:33,500
<i> Jade ran like crazy.</i>

12
00:00:33,633 --> 00:00:35,200
<i>What's happening to you? Ligaya!</i>

13
00:00:35,367 --> 00:00:37,267
<i>Bring her to Artemis Pharmacy's
stockroom.</i>

14
00:00:37,400 --> 00:00:38,733
<i> I'll send a doctor there.</i>

15
00:00:38,867 --> 00:00:40,567
<i>You brought Ligaya
to a hospital?</i>

16
00:00:40,700 --> 00:00:42,133
<i> I'm not concerned about her.</i>

17
00:00:44,467 --> 00:00:45,367
<i> That's Emma!</i>

18
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:46,133
<i> Ador?</i>

19
00:00:46,267 --> 00:00:47,667
<i> You can't escape me, Ligaya.</i>

20
00:00:47,800 --> 00:00:49,500
<i> Don't!</i>

21
00:00:49,633 --> 00:00:50,600
<i> Are you Jade's henchman?</i>

22
00:00:50,733 --> 00:00:51,567
<i> Help me!</i>

23
00:00:51,700 --> 00:00:53,100
<i> Look! They chain me!</i>

24
00:00:53,233 --> 00:00:53,900
<i>I brought you here
to the hospital.</i>

25
00:00:54,033 --> 00:00:55,733
<i>- Help me!
- She's lying!</i>

26
00:01:31,300 --> 00:01:34,233
Emma's here!
She's looking at me!

27
00:01:36,067 --> 00:01:37,867
Why are you staring at me?

28
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:38,667
I'm sorry.

29
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:39,600
What?

30
00:01:39,733 --> 00:01:41,167
Jade, come on.
Let's sit down first.

31
00:01:41,333 --> 00:01:42,767
You're working with Emma,
aren't you?

32
00:01:42,900 --> 00:01:43,500
My gosh.

33
00:01:43,633 --> 00:01:44,933
You are her men, aren't you?

34
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:49,200
Calm down.

35
00:01:50,700 --> 00:01:53,233
Jade, are you taking
your medicine?

36
00:01:54,367 --> 00:01:57,300
I haven't seen Emma since
I took my meds.

37
00:01:57,433 --> 00:01:58,167
But earlier...

38
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:00,967
That's Emma!

39
00:02:01,100 --> 00:02:02,433
There she is!

40
00:02:02,567 --> 00:02:04,500
There she is!
She's looking at me!

41
00:02:04,633 --> 00:02:06,367
Don't you have a mother
and grandmother?

42
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:08,133
She's lying!

43
00:02:08,267 --> 00:02:10,467
Stop it. That's enough.

44
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:11,567
Why are you fighting?

45
00:02:11,700 --> 00:02:14,633
Doctor, he's maltreating
the patient.

46
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:15,667
No.

47
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:18,900
They told me the patient
was already senile.

48
00:02:19,033 --> 00:02:20,500
Where's the patient?

49
00:02:20,633 --> 00:02:21,533
Where's the patient?

50
00:02:21,667 --> 00:02:23,833
She ran away.
You should've stayed out of it!

51
00:02:23,967 --> 00:02:26,533
We'll search for her.

52
00:02:26,667 --> 00:02:27,167
Okay.

53
00:02:29,767 --> 00:02:31,533
Why are you staring at me?

54
00:02:31,667 --> 00:02:34,033
Did Emma tell you to follow me?

55
00:02:34,167 --> 00:02:36,133
Did she tell you I was here?

56
00:02:38,567 --> 00:02:40,400
No!

57
00:02:41,633 --> 00:02:43,567
What do you need from me?

58
00:02:43,700 --> 00:02:45,133
Stay away!

59
00:02:45,267 --> 00:02:46,500
Hey!

60
00:02:46,633 --> 00:02:48,067
You're so loud!

61
00:02:48,233 --> 00:02:50,200
A kid here is sick!
You're such a bother!

62
00:02:52,167 --> 00:02:53,400
That's Emma!

63
00:02:53,533 --> 00:02:54,833
No!

64
00:02:54,967 --> 00:02:56,067
Stop!

65
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:57,967
Stop! Get out of here!

66
00:02:58,100 --> 00:02:59,500
No!

67
00:02:59,633 --> 00:03:01,467
No!

68
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:03,600
Are you here because Emma
told you?

69
00:03:03,733 --> 00:03:06,367
Did she pay you to do this
to me?

70
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:07,567
Stop!

71
00:03:07,700 --> 00:03:10,300
Stop! Don't look at me!

72
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:15,300
Why are you looking at me?
You! Emma!

73
00:03:15,433 --> 00:03:16,500
No!

74
00:03:16,633 --> 00:03:17,867
What are you talking about?
No one's attacking you.

75
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:18,800
Let's go.

76
00:03:18,933 --> 00:03:22,633
Emma's here. I saw her.

77
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,567
She's following me.

78
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:25,867
She's here.

79
00:03:27,033 --> 00:03:28,133
What?

80
00:03:28,267 --> 00:03:29,500
What do you need?

81
00:03:33,133 --> 00:03:34,667
Go on, Jade.

82
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,333
Go panic.

83
00:03:36,467 --> 00:03:37,667
Go insane.

84
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:40,567
That's not enough for what you
did to me.

85
00:03:41,667 --> 00:03:44,800
For making me crazy and for
stealing my husband and child.

86
00:03:55,533 --> 00:03:58,667
<i>Lord, I leave everything to you.</i>

87
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:00,533
<i> I need to get away from here.</i>

88
00:04:00,667 --> 00:04:03,433
<i>So that Danilo and Mookie
will know the truth.</i>

89
00:04:22,933 --> 00:04:24,067
Ligaya?

90
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:35,467
Logan?

91
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:39,367
Don't you have a meeting?

92
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:40,667
Why are you here?

93
00:04:43,367 --> 00:04:45,567
You wanted to make sure
I wouldn't fail?

94
00:04:46,967 --> 00:04:48,533
Relax.

95
00:04:48,667 --> 00:04:50,267
Relax, Emma.

96
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:52,933
I'm done with my first meeting.

97
00:04:53,067 --> 00:04:54,667
I just want to know
how you're doing.

98
00:04:56,433 --> 00:04:58,000
What happened to your haunting?

99
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:01,200
Wait.

100
00:05:05,933 --> 00:05:06,900
Look.

101
00:05:07,033 --> 00:05:08,500
<i> No!</i>

102
00:05:08,633 --> 00:05:10,000
<i> Stop!</i>

103
00:05:10,133 --> 00:05:11,700
<i> Stop! Get out of here!</i>

104
00:05:11,833 --> 00:05:13,367
<i> No!</i>

105
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:15,267
<i> No!</i>

106
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:16,433
<i>Did you come here because Emma
told you?</i>

107
00:05:16,567 --> 00:05:17,167
Oh, my.

108
00:05:18,100 --> 00:05:19,333
<i>Did she pay you
to do this to me?</i>

109
00:05:19,467 --> 00:05:20,267
Success.

110
00:05:22,533 --> 00:05:23,400
You know what?

111
00:05:23,533 --> 00:05:25,667
She reminded me of myself.

112
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:29,000
When I still had a bit
of sanity.

113
00:05:29,133 --> 00:05:31,133
Not knowing Jade was making me
crazy.

114
00:05:32,633 --> 00:05:34,900
Maybe she was also laughing
at me back then.

115
00:05:35,067 --> 00:05:37,000
Forget about that.

116
00:05:37,133 --> 00:05:42,000
It's now our turn
to laugh at her.

117
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:43,533
You impress me.

118
00:05:43,667 --> 00:05:45,500
You did your job without
a trace.

119
00:05:45,633 --> 00:05:47,433
That's why I didn't insist

120
00:05:47,567 --> 00:05:49,733
when you told me not
to come with you.

121
00:05:49,867 --> 00:05:50,833
Good job.

122
00:05:51,900 --> 00:05:53,867
I'm glad you trust me now.

123
00:05:55,067 --> 00:05:56,967
I thought you would always
follow me.

124
00:05:58,300 --> 00:06:02,600
Well, you almost failed just
once.

125
00:06:02,733 --> 00:06:05,433
At Activora's launch, remember?

126
00:06:06,433 --> 00:06:12,033
But, so far, your moves are
smooth.

127
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:14,633
So I let you do your thing.

128
00:06:16,633 --> 00:06:19,067
Logan, thank you.

129
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:20,800
This means a lot to me.

130
00:06:22,133 --> 00:06:24,500
I get more motivated
with what I do.

131
00:06:27,167 --> 00:06:28,633
Don't mention it.

132
00:06:28,767 --> 00:06:35,667
I know how important it is
to have someone who trusts you.

133
00:06:36,867 --> 00:06:39,333
Someone who always gets
involved in your life.

134
00:06:39,467 --> 00:06:40,633
Someone who critiques you.

135
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:43,333
Someone who always has
something to say about

136
00:06:43,467 --> 00:06:44,900
what you do.

137
00:06:45,033 --> 00:06:48,200
But also your number one fan.

138
00:06:48,333 --> 00:06:49,533
That's what I am to you.

139
00:06:52,133 --> 00:06:52,833
I'm sorry,

140
00:06:54,067 --> 00:06:56,867
but my mom is still
my number one critic.

141
00:06:58,267 --> 00:07:00,500
She's also the one who trusts me
the most.

142
00:07:03,567 --> 00:07:09,433
You'll get annoyed with her
if you meet her.

143
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:12,333
But you will love her.

144
00:07:14,733 --> 00:07:18,400
Too bad she isn't with me
anymore.

145
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:43,133
Maybe we should split.

146
00:07:43,267 --> 00:07:44,867
Okay, you can leave it to us.

147
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:45,867
Okay.

148
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,133
Go the other way, bro.
I'll go straight.

149
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:48,233
Hurry up.

150
00:07:56,800 --> 00:08:01,100
Miss, did you see a woman
wearing a white shirt?

151
00:08:01,233 --> 00:08:04,267
She's about this tall,
has chinky eyes,

152
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:05,800
and her hair is already white.

153
00:08:05,933 --> 00:08:08,100
No, I didn't.

154
00:08:08,233 --> 00:08:09,833
- Are you sure? Okay.
- Yes.

155
00:08:09,967 --> 00:08:11,333
Thank you.

156
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:16,000
Where did she go?

157
00:08:16,133 --> 00:08:18,333
I'll be in trouble.

158
00:08:18,467 --> 00:08:21,267
Bro, bro.

159
00:08:21,433 --> 00:08:23,733
I think I saw the woman
you're looking for.

160
00:08:23,867 --> 00:08:24,467
Really?

161
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:25,433
Yes.

162
00:08:27,567 --> 00:08:28,100
Bro, bro.

163
00:08:29,533 --> 00:08:31,567
I think I saw the woman
you're looking for.

164
00:08:31,700 --> 00:08:32,400
Really?

165
00:08:32,533 --> 00:08:33,433
Yes.

166
00:08:35,233 --> 00:08:36,333
She went that way.

167
00:08:36,467 --> 00:08:38,767
I ran into her earlier.

168
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:39,767
Are you sure?

169
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:40,533
Yes.

170
00:08:42,233 --> 00:08:44,533
- Okay, thank you.
- Thank you.

171
00:08:59,433 --> 00:09:02,867
I'm sorry, we have to drop
by another bar's branch.

172
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:03,767
It's okay.

173
00:09:03,900 --> 00:09:05,733
I need to get something.

174
00:09:08,033 --> 00:09:08,567
And,

175
00:09:09,667 --> 00:09:11,167
I'm sorry about earlier, too.

176
00:09:12,467 --> 00:09:14,400
I just remembered my mom.

177
00:09:15,633 --> 00:09:18,067
We were together when I was
worrying

178
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:20,133
about how to get Mookie back
from Olive.

179
00:09:21,433 --> 00:09:26,833
Even if we don't always get
along,

180
00:09:26,967 --> 00:09:29,667
she's been my number-one
supporter

181
00:09:29,833 --> 00:09:31,200
in getting Mookie back.

182
00:09:32,533 --> 00:09:38,333
Wherever she is, I'm sure
she always prays for me.

183
00:09:38,467 --> 00:09:40,967
Maybe that's why you came into
my life.

184
00:09:41,100 --> 00:09:42,600
God gave me you.

185
00:09:44,667 --> 00:09:46,667
I don't know how I can repay you

186
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:48,567
for all the kindness you've
shown me.

187
00:09:50,833 --> 00:09:52,400
So...

188
00:09:52,533 --> 00:09:57,500
are you saying I should charge
you?

189
00:09:57,633 --> 00:10:02,233
Of course, as long as I
can give you what you ask,

190
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:03,233
why not?

191
00:10:05,333 --> 00:10:09,967
I'll send you a bill after you
get Mookie back from Jade.

192
00:10:11,100 --> 00:10:12,767
Enough with my drama.

193
00:10:12,900 --> 00:10:16,267
You might be late for your
meeting at the Luna Vare Club.

194
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:18,833
Do you want me to come with you?

195
00:10:18,967 --> 00:10:20,267
Good idea.

196
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:21,433
I like that.

197
00:10:23,633 --> 00:10:25,133
I'll go there first.

198
00:10:25,267 --> 00:10:26,433
Stay here and wait for me.

199
00:10:26,567 --> 00:10:28,967
Sure. It's not that far.
I'll wait for you here.

200
00:10:31,967 --> 00:10:34,967
Hey, what are you thinking
about?

201
00:10:35,133 --> 00:10:36,633
Care to share?

202
00:10:38,733 --> 00:10:42,033
I think we should tell
our parents about us.

203
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:47,133
What's wrong?

204
00:10:47,267 --> 00:10:48,300
Don't you want to?

205
00:10:48,433 --> 00:10:50,000
No, of course not.

206
00:10:50,133 --> 00:10:55,367
Of course, I do. I mean,
Dad knows you already.

207
00:10:55,500 --> 00:10:57,467
And Aunt Jade is chill.

208
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:01,100
But I wish Mom would hear
the news, too.

209
00:11:02,900 --> 00:11:04,600
You know, Mooks?

210
00:11:04,733 --> 00:11:07,667
She's always in my prayers.
I mean Aunt Emma.

211
00:11:08,867 --> 00:11:10,100
I hope she comes back.

212
00:11:11,567 --> 00:11:13,800
Because even if you're
smiling,

213
00:11:13,933 --> 00:11:15,700
I can still see your sadness.

214
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:19,800
Your heart's emptiness that
Aunt Emma can only fill up.

215
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:26,133
Do you think my mom and I will
still see each other?

216
00:11:26,267 --> 00:11:27,367
I do.

217
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:30,167
And it's not just a someday
kind of way.

218
00:11:30,300 --> 00:11:33,800
But I think it'll happen soon.

219
00:11:33,933 --> 00:11:35,600
You'll see her soon.

220
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:38,767
Zayn!

221
00:11:40,167 --> 00:11:41,500
Mom!

222
00:11:41,667 --> 00:11:43,033
Is that your mom?

223
00:11:43,167 --> 00:11:44,033
Yes.

224
00:11:44,167 --> 00:11:44,933
Wait, I'll introduce you to her.

225
00:11:45,067 --> 00:11:45,900
Wait.

226
00:11:46,033 --> 00:11:47,700
Zayn, I'm not ready yet.

227
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:48,667
Chill.

228
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:50,200
I'll introduce you as a friend.

229
00:11:50,333 --> 00:11:52,533
It should be special once I
introduce you as my girlfriend.

230
00:11:52,667 --> 00:11:54,600
Wait, I'll talk to her first.

231
00:11:54,733 --> 00:11:56,400
Mommy!

232
00:11:56,533 --> 00:11:56,933
Mommy!

233
00:11:57,100 --> 00:11:58,533
Hello, darling.

234
00:12:02,767 --> 00:12:04,500
Hi, flirt.

235
00:12:04,633 --> 00:12:06,833
Stacy, not now.

236
00:12:06,967 --> 00:12:08,600
Why?

237
00:12:08,733 --> 00:12:10,433
I'm bored.

238
00:12:10,567 --> 00:12:12,733
I really want to play.

239
00:12:12,867 --> 00:12:13,733
I said no!

240
00:12:15,467 --> 00:12:16,533
Stacy!

241
00:12:16,667 --> 00:12:18,200
- Oh my God!
- My God, what happened?

242
00:12:18,333 --> 00:12:19,667
Auntie!

243
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:22,833
Zayn's girlfriend pushed me!

244
00:12:22,967 --> 00:12:25,400
Stop making up a story!

245
00:12:25,533 --> 00:12:27,867
I'm sorry,
but I didn't push her.

246
00:12:29,300 --> 00:12:34,567
Zayn, this girl is your
girlfriend?

247
00:12:50,867 --> 00:12:53,067
You really are useless, Caloy!

248
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,900
Find Ligaya!

249
00:12:57,033 --> 00:12:59,533
Don't stop until you find her!

250
00:12:59,667 --> 00:13:03,033
Because she'll expose me.

251
00:13:04,367 --> 00:13:05,733
- No!
- Jade.

252
00:13:05,867 --> 00:13:07,433
Why don't we report it
to the police?

253
00:13:07,567 --> 00:13:09,033
So we can find Miss Ligaya.

254
00:13:10,933 --> 00:13:13,933
Do you hear yourself, Leticia?

255
00:13:14,067 --> 00:13:15,333
Report it to the police?

256
00:13:16,700 --> 00:13:18,400
Then she'll report me too!

257
00:13:21,567 --> 00:13:24,033
You need to find Ligaya!

258
00:13:24,167 --> 00:13:26,267
Go back to the house
and wait for her!

259
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:29,200
She might go there,
and Danilo might see her!

260
00:13:29,333 --> 00:13:30,333
No!

261
00:13:30,467 --> 00:13:31,967
That can't happen.

262
00:13:32,100 --> 00:13:33,800
- Go!
- Go, Caloy. Go ahead.

263
00:13:36,033 --> 00:13:37,800
That can't happen.

264
00:13:37,933 --> 00:13:39,100
No.

265
00:13:44,367 --> 00:13:45,200
Emma.

266
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:49,833
She's here.

267
00:13:49,967 --> 00:13:51,900
- What's wrong with you?
- She hears us.

268
00:13:52,033 --> 00:13:54,967
Emma's here. She hears us.

269
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:57,700
Hey. Get ahold of yourself.

270
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,900
She did this.

271
00:14:01,033 --> 00:14:03,833
She wants to take everything
away from me.

272
00:14:05,167 --> 00:14:06,700
Come on.
Will you stop it already, Jade?

273
00:14:06,833 --> 00:14:07,500
No!

274
00:14:07,633 --> 00:14:08,800
- No!
- Emma's dead already.

275
00:14:08,933 --> 00:14:12,967
Didn't we see the photo from
Altair? Her body. She's dead.

276
00:14:13,100 --> 00:14:15,500
There's no proof
that Emma's dead.

277
00:14:19,367 --> 00:14:21,800
There's no proof
that Emma died.

278
00:14:24,100 --> 00:14:27,967
Altair might have conspired
with her.

279
00:14:30,133 --> 00:14:31,733
To toy with me.

280
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:36,233
That's impossible.

281
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:40,433
I'm sure Emma's alive.

282
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:43,267
She did all this.

283
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,667
She's haunting me.

284
00:14:50,033 --> 00:14:53,800
She's planned all this.

285
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:56,033
No.

286
00:14:59,333 --> 00:15:00,667
No.

287
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:09,067
Yes, Mommy.

288
00:15:10,533 --> 00:15:12,033
Mookie is my girlfriend.

289
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:25,967
Son,

290
00:15:27,033 --> 00:15:29,400
I am not against you having
a girlfriend

291
00:15:29,533 --> 00:15:31,367
because you're old enough.
Right?

292
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:39,800
But I hope you'll be with
someone presentable

293
00:15:39,967 --> 00:15:41,733
and with grace.

294
00:15:44,233 --> 00:15:48,133
Not with someone who seems
to be getting into a bar fight.

295
00:15:48,267 --> 00:15:49,133
Mom!

296
00:15:49,267 --> 00:15:51,133
That's not fair.

297
00:15:51,267 --> 00:15:52,600
I am being honest.

298
00:15:52,733 --> 00:15:55,600
I say what I see.

299
00:15:55,733 --> 00:15:57,233
Mookie isn't like that.

300
00:15:58,367 --> 00:16:00,033
Stacy is the bully.

301
00:16:00,167 --> 00:16:02,567
Zayn, I'm the one who's hurt
here.

302
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:04,833
She really pushed me!

303
00:16:04,967 --> 00:16:06,333
I don't believe you, Stacy.

304
00:16:07,367 --> 00:16:10,867
Didn't I tell you to stay away
from her?

305
00:16:11,033 --> 00:16:12,200
Zayn!

306
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:13,700
What has gotten into you?

307
00:16:13,833 --> 00:16:16,733
Is that what this girl teaches
you?

308
00:16:16,867 --> 00:16:17,967
Violence?

309
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,033
Even towards women?

310
00:16:20,167 --> 00:16:22,400
I'm just defending
my girlfriend.

311
00:16:22,533 --> 00:16:24,500
Stacy is such a liar.

312
00:16:26,367 --> 00:16:28,133
And you're talking back to me.

313
00:16:28,267 --> 00:16:29,700
Mommy, no!

314
00:16:29,833 --> 00:16:31,267
Zayn!

315
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:32,500
Zayn, it's okay.

316
00:16:33,933 --> 00:16:35,700
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

317
00:16:35,833 --> 00:16:37,200
I'll go ahead.

318
00:16:38,533 --> 00:16:39,167
Mooks.

319
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:43,467
Zayn, I need to talk to you.

320
00:16:49,700 --> 00:16:53,600
Is this part of your evil plan
to get back at Mookie?

321
00:16:53,733 --> 00:16:55,567
Of course.

322
00:16:55,700 --> 00:16:58,967
I told Mom to bring
my godmother here.

323
00:16:59,100 --> 00:17:01,300
Because I knew they'd be here.

324
00:17:01,433 --> 00:17:03,100
I heard them yesterday.

325
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:14,900
Hello?

326
00:17:16,133 --> 00:17:17,567
You miss me, don't you?

327
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:20,967
What do you need?

328
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:22,467
Here we go.

329
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:23,533
Is it money?

330
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:24,933
How much do you need?

331
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:28,467
Just kidding, Mom.

332
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:30,767
You miss your naughty child,
don't you?

333
00:17:33,033 --> 00:17:35,667
I'll visit you when
I'm no longer busy.

334
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:37,633
Don't be upset.

335
00:17:39,233 --> 00:17:40,433
Wait.

336
00:17:40,567 --> 00:17:43,200
What are you still doing there?
Go on inside.

337
00:17:43,333 --> 00:17:46,633
I feel envious.
You're talking with your mother.

338
00:17:46,767 --> 00:17:49,667
Your bravado disappears
when you're talking to her.

339
00:17:51,100 --> 00:17:53,133
Fine. I'm sweet with my mom.

340
00:17:54,567 --> 00:17:55,933
Do what you need to do.

341
00:17:58,367 --> 00:17:59,367
Why did you call?

342
00:18:01,067 --> 00:18:03,400
I'm at work. Soon.

343
00:18:05,233 --> 00:18:09,467
Don't forget your maintenance
meds.

344
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:10,800
You're hanging up already?

345
00:18:12,167 --> 00:18:13,667
You'll just play mahjong.

346
00:18:15,433 --> 00:18:16,367
Bye.

347
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:17,633
Love you, Mom.

348
00:18:23,567 --> 00:18:24,433
Ma'am?

349
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:27,933
Ma'am, are you okay?

350
00:18:32,567 --> 00:18:34,633
Are you okay?

351
00:18:34,767 --> 00:18:36,033
It's okay.

352
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:39,700
You look so tired.

353
00:18:39,833 --> 00:18:41,600
Do you want water?

354
00:18:41,733 --> 00:18:43,400
Sorry, this is all we have.

355
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:48,833
It's clean.

356
00:18:50,067 --> 00:18:51,200
Thank you.

357
00:18:59,433 --> 00:19:01,100
Come with me to my car.

358
00:19:01,233 --> 00:19:03,000
I'll give you money to buy
something to eat.

359
00:19:03,133 --> 00:19:03,800
Come on.

360
00:19:05,367 --> 00:19:06,500
You're so weak.

361
00:19:08,500 --> 00:19:10,267
Sorry, it stings.

362
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:15,267
Madam, what happened here?

363
00:19:17,933 --> 00:19:19,667
Please help me.

364
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:21,733
I need your help.

365
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:32,500
I need your help.

366
00:19:32,633 --> 00:19:33,267
Help?

367
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:35,300
Oh, my.

368
00:19:35,433 --> 00:19:36,467
Sorry, Ma'am.

369
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:36,933
Sorry.

370
00:19:37,067 --> 00:19:37,667
Sorry.

371
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:40,033
Someone's chasing me.

372
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:46,433
What kind of help do you need?

373
00:19:52,467 --> 00:19:54,800
- It's okay.
- I'm sorry again, Ma'am.

374
00:19:54,933 --> 00:19:56,133
I'm sorry.

375
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:00,833
Thank you.

376
00:20:00,967 --> 00:20:03,433
I'll give you money so you can
buy food.

377
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:08,000
Mom!

378
00:20:08,133 --> 00:20:09,033
Ma'am, where are you going?

379
00:20:11,967 --> 00:20:14,833
I'll give you some money to buy
food.

380
00:20:14,967 --> 00:20:15,633
Mom!

381
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:38,733
Logan!

382
00:20:40,433 --> 00:20:42,867
Who was that woman
you talked to?

383
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,333
I don't know.

384
00:20:44,467 --> 00:20:47,100
She asked for help,
but she suddenly left.

385
00:20:47,233 --> 00:20:48,567
I don't know why.

386
00:20:50,767 --> 00:20:53,100
My heart is racing.

387
00:20:53,233 --> 00:20:55,933
That woman reminded me
of my mom.

388
00:20:57,167 --> 00:20:58,333
Relax.

389
00:20:58,600 --> 00:21:00,633
Maybe you feel that way

390
00:21:00,767 --> 00:21:02,300
because you've been thinking
about her.

391
00:21:04,967 --> 00:21:06,033
Maybe you're right.

392
00:21:08,367 --> 00:21:13,433
I hope Mom is doing well
wherever she is.

393
00:21:15,933 --> 00:21:21,100
But I'll be more at peace
if I see and be with her.

394
00:21:34,867 --> 00:21:35,900
Mookie.

395
00:21:38,467 --> 00:21:40,833
Mooks, can we talk?

396
00:21:40,967 --> 00:21:42,767
- Are you okay?
- You can go, Flor.

397
00:21:42,933 --> 00:21:44,200
I'll be right there.

398
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:48,200
Mookie, can we talk about
what happened?

399
00:21:50,567 --> 00:21:52,067
Zayn, I'm done with it.

400
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:53,300
What?

401
00:21:53,433 --> 00:21:54,500
No!

402
00:21:54,633 --> 00:21:56,667
You can't give up
just like that.

403
00:21:58,133 --> 00:21:59,967
But I really messed up.

404
00:22:00,100 --> 00:22:02,200
It's because of Stacy.

405
00:22:02,333 --> 00:22:04,033
She did that on purpose.

406
00:22:04,167 --> 00:22:06,233
She intended to put you down
in front of my mom.

407
00:22:06,367 --> 00:22:07,200
Zayn,

408
00:22:09,233 --> 00:22:10,633
don't you see me?

409
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:14,900
Look at me.

410
00:22:15,067 --> 00:22:17,567
My hair, my makeup...

411
00:22:19,433 --> 00:22:22,167
Your mother ended up having
a bad impression of me.

412
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:25,933
Maybe if she had met
the old Mookie.

413
00:22:26,067 --> 00:22:26,767
Mookie, stop.

414
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:30,067
Why are you so affected?

415
00:22:32,067 --> 00:22:35,000
Let's forget what Mommy said,
okay?

416
00:22:35,133 --> 00:22:36,767
Zayn, what's wrong with you?

417
00:22:36,900 --> 00:22:38,867
Of course, it matters to me!

418
00:22:41,833 --> 00:22:44,567
I want to get your mom's
approval.

419
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:53,833
Because if not, she might end up
not liking me.

420
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:56,433
Because I look like a bad girl.

421
00:22:56,567 --> 00:22:58,267
<i> Emma's not coming back.</i>

422
00:22:58,400 --> 00:22:59,100
<i> You know what?</i>

423
00:22:59,233 --> 00:23:00,667
<i> It makes a lot of sense.</i>

424
00:23:00,800 --> 00:23:04,200
<i>She left because she went
with another man.</i>

425
00:23:04,333 --> 00:23:06,600
<i> It's about time we accept</i>

426
00:23:06,733 --> 00:23:08,867
<i>that Emma's not coming back
anymore.</i>

427
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:11,100
<i> She's never coming back.</i>

428
00:23:11,233 --> 00:23:13,367
And then what, Zayn?

429
00:23:13,500 --> 00:23:15,433
She'll reject me, too.

430
00:23:16,833 --> 00:23:21,200
Zayn, I don't want
to experience it again,

431
00:23:21,333 --> 00:23:23,833
especially with your mom.

432
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:26,433
Mom doesn't know you yet.

433
00:23:26,567 --> 00:23:29,200
But I do.

434
00:23:31,100 --> 00:23:33,200
And I'll make her see
the real you.

435
00:23:34,267 --> 00:23:37,467
You're the kindest person
I've ever met.

436
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:40,533
The sweetest...

437
00:23:40,667 --> 00:23:42,333
The most caring...

438
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:45,700
And definitely, the most loving.

439
00:23:47,733 --> 00:23:49,733
So, I'll introduce you again
to Mom.

440
00:23:50,867 --> 00:23:52,633
But this time,

441
00:23:52,767 --> 00:23:54,467
as the real Mookie.

442
00:23:57,667 --> 00:24:00,200
The girl I fell in love with.

443
00:24:01,567 --> 00:24:02,633
Okay, Mooks?

444
00:24:04,167 --> 00:24:06,067
You and me, okay?

445
00:24:09,067 --> 00:24:10,533
You and me.

446
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:21,033
Are you serious?

447
00:24:21,167 --> 00:24:22,933
Did you really have Emma's grave
dug up?

448
00:24:23,067 --> 00:24:26,100
I told you, Emma's not dead yet.

449
00:24:30,333 --> 00:24:31,167
Shut up!

450
00:24:32,600 --> 00:24:33,467
Shut up!

451
00:24:38,067 --> 00:24:39,833
I'm getting worried about you.

452
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:46,267
What are you doing?

453
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:48,300
Why did you stop digging?

454
00:24:48,433 --> 00:24:52,533
Ma'am, there's no soil to dig.
These are all rocks.

455
00:24:52,667 --> 00:24:53,533
No!

456
00:24:53,667 --> 00:24:55,333
Keep digging!

457
00:24:55,467 --> 00:24:58,500
I don't care if Emma's body
is already decomposing.

458
00:24:58,633 --> 00:25:02,233
I want to see that she will
never rise from that grave!

459
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:04,400
There's nothing we can do.
We can't dig deeper.

460
00:25:04,533 --> 00:25:06,767
You're so useless!

461
00:25:08,367 --> 00:25:09,300
Jade.

462
00:25:09,433 --> 00:25:11,000
Give me that!

463
00:25:11,133 --> 00:25:11,967
Jade.

464
00:25:14,333 --> 00:25:16,467
Where the hell are you, Emma?

465
00:25:16,600 --> 00:25:17,900
Show me yourself!

466
00:25:21,100 --> 00:25:23,333
Show me yourself! Darn you!

467
00:25:29,800 --> 00:25:30,700
Ma'am Jade.

468
00:25:39,500 --> 00:25:41,167
Is Emma not here?

469
00:25:41,300 --> 00:25:42,967
Her body's not here.

470
00:25:43,100 --> 00:25:44,667
Aren't you going
to show yourself?

471
00:25:47,367 --> 00:25:48,200
<i> Emma?</i>

472
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:53,633
<i> You're not real. You're dead.</i>

473
00:25:53,767 --> 00:25:55,533
<i> I'm sure you're already dead.</i>

474
00:25:55,667 --> 00:25:57,467
<i> Because you killed me.</i>

475
00:25:59,533 --> 00:26:01,133
<i> That's Emma!</i>

476
00:26:01,267 --> 00:26:04,567
No!

477
00:26:06,067 --> 00:26:09,933
So that means the one I
see...

478
00:26:11,300 --> 00:26:12,833
the one who's haunting me...

479
00:26:14,567 --> 00:26:16,100
is Emma.

480
00:26:17,467 --> 00:26:18,900
She's fooling me.

481
00:26:20,433 --> 00:26:21,833
She's scaring me.

482
00:26:23,433 --> 00:26:24,833
I won't allow that.

483
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:30,267
I won't let a lowly Emma
fool me!

484
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:31,900
No!

485
00:26:34,700 --> 00:26:35,733
Jade!

486
00:26:37,933 --> 00:26:40,067
No!

487
00:26:44,500 --> 00:26:46,867
You, traitor.

488
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:48,200
What do you need from me?

489
00:26:48,333 --> 00:26:49,367
Emma.

490
00:26:49,500 --> 00:26:55,000
You're not only a bad
husband...

491
00:26:55,133 --> 00:26:58,033
You really are a bad person.

492
00:26:58,167 --> 00:27:00,333
I will do everything for you,
Ligaya.

493
00:27:00,467 --> 00:27:08,233
Even if I feel that you don't
trust me.

494
00:27:08,367 --> 00:27:10,133
Don't! Don't!

495
00:27:15,033 --> 00:27:16,800
Flor, get out there now!

496
00:27:16,967 --> 00:27:17,933
What? Why?

497
00:27:18,067 --> 00:27:19,733
Jade already knows I'm alive.

498
00:27:19,867 --> 00:27:20,633
What?

499
00:27:20,767 --> 00:27:22,767
Hurry.

500
00:27:22,900 --> 00:27:24,300
Be discreet.

501
00:27:24,433 --> 00:27:25,867
She might do something bad
to you.
